<p>Africa’s first G20 leaders’ summit opened on Saturday with a focus on putting poorer nations’ challenges at the center of talks [france24.com#3][abcnews.go.com#1][pbs.org#1]. The United States is absent after President Donald Trump ordered a boycott, but hosts say efforts to adopt a summit declaration are moving ahead [france24.com#3][abcnews.go.com#1][aljazeera.com#1][thehindu.com#2]. The meeting is in Johannesburg [nytimes.com#1], and discussions are shaped by calls for a multilateral approach to global threats, debate over Trump’s unilateral Ukraine plan, and deadlock at COP30 climate talks in Brazil [france24.com#2][france24.com#3].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/WJcnajpPCWEe3oOANzvhtSwhA9V_FtWHR-lAGj7C6ywsNIqt3ltpq9tW-ZM32wIZnImAAEDTPOWzCZ3FeMrZgGMcIbyAmjzwOrYGNOBw2Ak3I7ReaFslBdIat1YV0dhGxaqPbTxLEiA06BEfkKAxZNp7qx3SfwAvtOFmqTLFpQ' alt='Leaders gather in Johannesburg for Africa’s first G20 summit.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>United States stance: The U.S. is boycotting the two-day meeting at President Trump’s direction; a senior White House official called a draft declaration prepared without U.S. input “shameful” [france24.com#2][abcnews.go.com#1][straitstimes.com#1].</li><li>Host priorities: South Africa aims to push an ambitious agenda centered on the problems of poorer countries, with a particular focus on climate change impacts on developing nations; elements of this agenda have met U.S. resistance [abcnews.go.com#1][pbs.org#1][thehindu.com#1].</li><li>Declaration push: Despite the rift, South Africa says there is “overwhelming consensus” to adopt a summit declaration, and a draft was prepared without U.S. input [thehindu.com#2][straitstimes.com#1].</li><li>Civil society voice: Protesters are using the summit to draw attention to domestic problems [nytimes.com#1].</li><li>Wider context: Leaders stressed a multilateral approach amid debate over Trump’s unilateral Ukraine plan and the ongoing deadlock at COP30 in Brazil [france24.com#2][france24.com#3].</li></ul><blockquote>There is overwhelming consensus that one of summit&#x27;s tasks is to adopt a declaration, - South Africa&#x27;s President</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>South African government: Hosts say they are preserving the G20’s integrity and report “overwhelming consensus” to adopt a declaration [thehindu.com#2]. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/g20-summit-south-africa-pm-modi-visit-trump-live-updates-november-22-2025/article70310266.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>United States administration: Washington is boycotting at President Trump’s direction; a senior official called a draft without U.S. input “shameful” [straitstimes.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/g20-leaders-meet-in-south-africa-seeking-agreement-despite-us-boycott'>The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>G20 attendees: Leaders emphasized putting the problems of the world’s poorest nations high on the agenda and stressed a multilateral approach [abcnews.go.com#1][france24.com#3]. (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/africas-g20-summit-opens-ambitious-agenda-move-trumps-127774970'>ABC News; France 24</a>)</li><li>Protesters in South Africa: Civil society groups are using the summit’s spotlight to highlight domestic problems [nytimes.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/11/21/world/africa/south-africa-g20-protests.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li><li>France 24 reporting: Coverage highlights emphasis on a multilateral approach amid debates over Trump’s Ukraine plan and the COP30 deadlock [france24.com#2][france24.com#3]. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20251122-g20-summit-opens-in-south-africa-without-trump'>France 24</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/g20-leaders-meet-in-south-africa-seeking-agreement-despite-us-boycott'>G20 leaders meet in South Africa seeking agreement, despite US boycott</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytim